SIMPLE: patella
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Patella
<hw>Pa*tel"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Patell⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a small pan, the
kneepan, dim. of <ets>patina</ets>, <ets>patena</ets>, a pan,
dish.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small dish, pan, or vase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The kneecap; the kneepan; the cap
of the knee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of marine gastropods,
including many species of limpets. The shell has the form of a flattened
cone. The common European limpet (<spn>Patella vulgata</spn>) is largely
used for food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of apothecium in lichens,
which is orbicular, flat, and sessile, and has a special rim not a part
of the thallus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Patellar</ent>⟦br⟧
